snippet.textDisplay: The biggest focus is money. The more diversity they have, the more viewers there will be, hence the more money they will make. How about a more in depth look at the clone wars? Between episodes 2 and 3, when the republic was thriving, giving a more realistic look rather than the animated series. Or a movie based on Obi-wan, from the ending of episode 2 right through to episode 4, showing new scenes before and after 66. I don’t know maybe I’m old school, but the sequels didn’t feel like Star Wars. What makes the original trilogy so intriguing is knowing and seeing what happened before order 66. The greatest war of the galaxy, and what shaped episodes 4, 5 and 6. Seeing all the protagonists and antagonists back again would just be a nice gesture after butchering the sequels. But it’s Disney, so either way it wouldn’t be the same..
